# Storybook Scaffold Patterns

## File 1: Component Shell (.tsx)
```tsx
// [ComponentName].tsx
import React from 'react';
import styles from './[ComponentName].module.css';

export interface [ComponentName]Props {
  // Props derived directly from intake spec — one per declared prop
  variant?: 'default' | 'compact'; // example — use actual variants
  // [TODO: add remaining props]
}

export const [ComponentName]: React.FC<[ComponentName]Props> = ({
  variant = 'default',
  ...props
}) => {
  return (
    <div
      className={styles.root}
      data-variant={variant}
      // [TODO: implement component logic]
    >
      {/* [TODO: implement component content] */}
    </div>
  );
};
```

## File 2: CSS Module (use validated tokens only)
```css
/* [ComponentName].module.css */
.root {
  /* Only use validated CSS variable tokens — no hardcoded values */
  color: var(--[token-css-var]);
  /* [TODO: wire up remaining tokens] */
}
```

## File 3: Stories File (CSF 3.0)
```tsx
// [ComponentName].stories.tsx
import type { Meta, StoryObj } from '@storybook/react';
import { [ComponentName] } from './[ComponentName]';

const meta: Meta<typeof [ComponentName]> = {
  title: 'Components/[ComponentName]',
  component: [ComponentName],
  argTypes: {
    // argTypes derived from props interface
  },
};
export default meta;
type Story = StoryObj<typeof [ComponentName]>;

// One story per variant declared in the intake spec
export const Default: Story = { args: { variant: 'default' } };
export const Compact: Story = { args: { variant: 'compact' } };
// [TODO: add remaining variant stories]
```

## File 4: Test Skeleton
```tsx
// [ComponentName].test.tsx
import { render } from '@testing-library/react';
import { [ComponentName] } from './[ComponentName]';

describe('[ComponentName]', () => {
  it('renders default variant', () => {
    // [TODO: add assertion]
  });
  // [TODO: add one test per variant]
});
```

## Rules
- Reference only validated tokens — never a flagged or unresolved token
- Use exact component name, prop names, and variant names from the intake spec
- Keep the scaffold minimal — the goal is a working shell, not a full implementation
